      • executeCommands

        private void executeCommands()
        Private helper method. Continuously reads lines from input, parses them in commands and parameters and executes the commands through the objects in the hash map.

      • parseParameters

        private java.lang.String[] parseParameters​(java.lang.String command,
                                           java.lang.String parametersString)
        Private helper method. Checks the command and parses the parameters based on it.
        Parameters:
        command - The actual command name, represented as a name.
        parametersString - The whole command line (contains both the command and the parameters), represented as a string.
        Returns:
        The parameters, represented as an array of strings.

      • closeOutputStreams

        private void closeOutputStreams()
        Private helper method. Closes the output and print streams, if they have been opened.

      • setSystemOutput

        private void setSystemOutput​(java.lang.String out,
                             java.lang.String err)
        Private helper method. Initialises the output and print streams.
        Parameters:
        out - The filename of the file that the standard output streams will be opened with, represented as a string.
        err - The filename of the file that the error streams will be opened with, represented as a string.

      • initCommands

        private void initCommands()
        Private helper method. Initialises the commands map with all possible commands. New commands can be easily added with the help of this method.
